===Etymology===
From {{etyl|NL.|en}} {{term|ephemerus}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|ἐφήμερος|tr=ephēmeros|lang=grc}}, the more common form of {{term|ἐφημέριος||of, for, or during the day, living or lasting but for a day, short-lived, temporary|tr=ephemerios|lang=grc}}, from {{term|ἐπί||on|tr=epi|lang=grc}} + {{term|ἡμέρα||day|tr=hēmera|lang=grc}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ɛˈfɛ.mə.ɹəl/|/əˈfɛ.mə.ɹəl/}}
* {{audio|en-us-ephemeral.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Something which lasts for a [[short]] period of [[time]].

====Synonyms====
* {{sense|short-lived}} [[ephemeron]]

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Lasting for a [[short]] period of [[time]].
